  "prompt": "I didn't kiss on the first date, is this bad and what should I do from this point on?",
  "response": "Not kissing on the first date is completely normal and not necessarily a bad thing. Many people prefer to take things slow and build a connection before becoming more physical. Here are a few tips on what to do moving forward:\n\n1. **Reflect on the Date**: Think about how the date went overall. Did you both enjoy each other's company? If so, that's a good sign.\n\n2. **Communicate**: If you felt a connection but didn't kiss, it's okay to bring it up casually in future conversations. Something as simple as, \"I had a great time; I hope it didn't feel weird not kissing,\" can open the door to discussing it.\n\n3. **Gauge Interest**: Pay attention to how your date reacts in subsequent interactions. If they seem interested and engaged, that\u2019s a positive sign.\n\n4. **Plan Another Date**: If you're interested, suggest another outing. A follow-up date can create more opportunities for intimacy and connection.\n\n5. **Be Yourself**: Focus on being genuine and comfortable. If a kiss happens organically on the next date, it will feel more natural.\n\n6. **Don\u2019t Stress About It**: Remember that every relationship develops at its own pace. Be patient and let things unfold naturally.\n\nUltimately, the most important thing is how both of you feel about each other, so focus on building that connection.",
